data.text:
We are looking to eliminate the "fear factor" in the food supply chain. 
More on #FairFoodChain:
  → On our webpage https://t.co/6cXGSYky0z
  → In our press release https://t.co/RJOCViWfWJ
  → In our memo https://t.co/rx9pT7CFRr 
  → For more, follow @EUAgri https://t.co/lVuYojC7So

Our proposals on #FairFoodChain presented today build on your ideas! 
We listened to the 1500+ varied contributions you gave to our public consultations on how to improve the food supply chain. Your voice matters! → https://t.co/6cXGSYky0z #EUHaveYourSay https://t.co/KVgvG6nFKv

We want to ban unfair trading practices, which are:
💶 Late payments for perishable food 
⏲️ Last minute order cancellations
📝 Unilateral/retroactive changes to contracts
🗑️ Forcing the supplier to pay for wasted products 
→ Learn more https://t.co/6cXGSYky0z #FairFoodChain https://t.co/ofTmq5M196

There are imbalances of bargaining power in the food supply chain.
Against this background, we are proposing minimum standards to make sure that operators compete on fair terms → https://t.co/31VfbnvuDd #FairFoodChain https://t.co/SffjXCoTjI

Any chain is only as strong as its weakest link. That's why an effective food supply chain is a #FairFoodChain
We propose to ban the more damaging unfair trading practices in the food supply chain → https://t.co/RJOCViWfWJ https://t.co/BRVwkLxUIs

88% of Europeans think that strengthening farmers' role in the food supply chain is important.
Later today, we will present our proposal for #FairFoodChain. https://t.co/2jVWPMowbs

Does your city care about values in trade? 
EU cities now have a new way of promoting their ideas on ethical trade with our #TradeCityAward. Apply by 20 April → https://t.co/lUNjukp2rC https://t.co/9UAvDigbq6

"The Facebook scandal has three aspects:
→ #DataProtection: we are equipped to remedy the situation with #GDPR
→ Fraud: national authorities have to address it with criminal justice
→ Electoral freedom: we need to know more about what happened" says Commissioner @VeraJourova https://t.co/1SUpSrDoCH

We have delivered over 80% of the #TeamJunckerEU proposals on consumer policy so far. More on our New Deal for Consumers in
→ Our press release https://t.co/RQOK7AHTaq  
→ Our memo https://t.co/2Gi5apOIXr
→ Our factsheets https://t.co/0BAs7kwYRA
→ Follow @EU_Consumer https://t.co/r2D5AmSk9z

Last, our New Deal for Consumers is about coordination:
⚙ National: EU countries will have the power to impose dissuasive penalties up to 4 % of the trader’s annual turnover
🌍 International: we will seek to develop cooperation projects with key trading partners
#EU4Consumers https://t.co/baOfZB6qwg

Our New Deal for Consumers is about tackling #DualFoodQuality:
🍫 EU Law: we are making it explicit in EU Law that marketing products in the same branding and packaging, while offering different product composition is an unfair commercial practice
#EU4Consumers https://t.co/we8e2kI8LX

Our New Deal for Consumers is about redress:
💶 Individual remedies: you will be able to claim for compensation when affected by unfair commercial practices
⚖ Collective redress: consumer organisations will be allowed to seek compensation for a group of consumers
 #EU4Consumers https://t.co/fsDI3sOVrf

Our New Deal for Consumers is about transparency:
📦 in online marketplaces: you will be clearly informed whether you buy from a professional or a consumer
🔎 on search results: you will know when a search result is being paid for by a trader
#EU4Consumers https://t.co/AbT8lji2xc

Our New Deal for Consumers is about rights:
🖥 Free Digital Services: you will be able to freely cancel your account within 14 days, even if the service is free
🚪 Doorstep-selling: EU countries will be allowed to adopt rules to prevent unsolicited visits by traders
#EU4Consumers https://t.co/m5ZRKSE09R

Today, we propose a New Deal for Consumers. 
It will give you stronger consumer rights and additional tools to get redress if your rights are violated. What is in it for you? → https://t.co/RQOK7AHTaq  #EU4consumers https://t.co/4aHIzot95N

How will today's proposal increase the transparency of scientific studies in response to the citizens' initiative?
• Questions & answers → https://t.co/sm4YUmFV2W
• For more, follow → @Food_EU
#foodchain #EUTakeTheInitiative #ECI https://t.co/U9tg64HXFa

Europe has a solid basis for the future.
Our new #DataProtection rules will enter into application on 25 May. This will represent a shift in how companies process data in the EU → https://t.co/Bn9SEBtXUf #GDPR https://t.co/LGgVMtIOqR

We cannot accept that in parts of Europe, lower quality food is sold despite identical packaging.
We will tackle the issue of #DualFoodQuality in our New Deal for Consumers to be presented later today. #EU4consumers https://t.co/9WhwBdFbQ8
